# Atlassian MCP Integration Configuration Example
# Copy these settings to your backend/.env file and fill in your credentials

# Confluence Configuration (optional - only if using Confluence)
# For Cloud: Use https://your-domain.atlassian.net/wiki
# For Server: Use https://your-server.com/confluence
CONFLUENCE_URL=https://your-company.atlassian.net/wiki
CONFLUENCE_USERNAME=your.email@company.com
CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN=your_confluence_api_token_here

# Jira Configuration (optional - only if using Jira)  
# For Cloud: Use https://your-domain.atlassian.net
# For Server: Use https://your-server.com/jira
JIRA_URL=https://your-company.atlassian.net
JIRA_USERNAME=your.email@company.com
JIRA_API_TOKEN=your_jira_api_token_here

# Notes:
# 1. You can configure just Jira, just Confluence, or both
# 2. For Atlassian Cloud, use your email as username
# 3. Generate API tokens at: https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens
# 4. For Server/Data Center, use Personal Access Tokens instead
# 5. The integration will only enable if at least one set of credentials is provided